<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 03 at 7:10PM CDT  by NWS QuadCities</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of south central
Whiteside, northeastern Henry and northwestern Bureau Counties
through 745 PM CDT...
At 709 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Geneseo, or 11 miles north of Cambridge, moving east at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Atkinson, Annawan and Hooppole.
This includes Interstate 80 in Illinois between mile markers 17 and
41.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
